# CEX Nucleus Definition (N00-N07)

A CEX nucleus is a self-contained, fractal subsystem implementing 1 of 7 core functions:

- **N00** (Genesis): Archetypal framework for creating new nuclei  
- **N01** (Intelligence): Research/analysis with 200K token context  
- **N02** (Marketing): Copywriting with 200K token context  
- **N03** (Builder): Code/test/deploy with 1M token context  
- **N04** (Knowledge): Documentation with 200K token context  
- **N05** (Code): Code testing with 200K token context  
- **N07** (Orchestration): Multi-nucleus coordination  

Each nucleus owns 12 pillars (P01-P12) and implements:

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| nucleus_id | N00-N07 identifier |
| role | Core function (Genesis, Research, etc.) |
| pillars_owned | P01-P12 implementation |
| sin_lens | 8F pipeline compliance |
| cli_binding | Command-line interface |
| model_tier | Model capability tier |
| boot_script | Startup automation |
| agent_card_path | Subagent configuration |
| crew_templates_exposed | Template availability |
| domain_agents | Specialized subagents |

The fractal structure mirrors N00's 12 pillars, creating a recursive architecture for scalable knowledge systems.
